• Assumption: the elements a[i] are uniformly distributed over the
interval [0, 1)
• Principle:
• divide the interval [0, 1) in n subintervals of equal sizes, indexed from 0
to n − 1;
• distribute the elements a[i] in the corresponding interval: (cid:98)n · a[i](cid:99);
• sort each package using another method;
• combine the n packages in a sorted list.
